 Description:
 This program directly supports Marine Corps Force Design efforts by providing expeditionary operations centers and mission planning and briefing spaces at the proper security classification level to the Fleet
 Marine Forces (FMF), enabling the Marine Corps Stand in Force (SIF) to rapidly incorporate classified capabilities within the Joint Force. The establishment of mobile infrastructure will enable the FMF to plug in-
 and-out in an inconspicuous manner, increasing both capability and capacity of individual Marines as producers and consumers to support timely and accurate decision making during networked operations.

 ICD 705 Compliant Deployable Secure Shelters-Scalable (DS3) is the deployable component of the ICD-705 compliant facilities. This program will provide a deployable, dual-accredited Temporary-Sensitive
 Compartmented Information Facility (T-SCIF) solution for the fleet to employ in an Expeditionary Advanced Base Operations (EABO) setting.




