INSERT INTO public.proc_line_narratives (proc_line_id, fiscal_year, mission_description, justification, raw_text, source_pdf, source_page_description, source_page_amount, content_hash, ingested_at) VALUES ($$P_0300_L020$$, 2026, $$This exhibit showcases capabilities and services from across various Defense Information Systems Agency (DISA) Directorates. These diverse offerings are unified by their collective objective: to construct a
 resilient and agile warfighter support system that secures a decisive competitive advantage over adversaries. Significantly, modernization efforts led by Field Commands and Offices directly support the strategic
 priority of rebuilding the military by upgrading critical infrastructure.

 White House Situation Support Staff (WHSSS)

 Operating under Presidential direction, the DISA WHSSS provides essential financial and personnel resources. The WHSSS delivers critical IT and communication services to the National Security Council
 (NSC), including the 24/7 White House Situation Room (WHSR). The WHSR is indispensable for providing global situational awareness, facilitating crisis management, and enabling executive communication for
 the President (POTUS) as Commander-in-Chief, Head of State, and Chief Executive, as well as supporting the Vice President (VPOTUS) and key White House staff.

 This funding request is crucial for modernizing the WHSR's core information, audio-visual, and communication infrastructure. Specifically, it enables upgrades to the intelligence watch floor and virtual
 conferencing operations. The investment will also extend WHSR's intelligence support globally for special mission travel and residential requirements, while empowering WHSSS to establish secure virtual
 communication with foreign leaders, directly bolstering presidential policy coordination.

 Field Commands and Field Offices (FC/FO)

 The DISA FC/FO ensure the Department of War Information Network (DoWIN)—encompassing voice, video, and data services—aligns with the Joint Cyber Warfighting Architecture (JCWA). This alignment
 directly supports global warfighter needs across all phases of conflict.

 The FC/FO program funds DISA employee support for Combatant Commanders and Combatant Command (CCMD) staff, facilitating the integration of DISA services within Joint All-Domain Operations (JADO)
 Operational Plans (OPLANS). The IT, facility/space accommodations, and programmatic operational support at each CCMD and National Military Command Center (NMCC) Headquarters (HQ) worldwide.
 Furthermore, the FC/FO program establishes on-site strategic Command and Control (C2) and situational awareness among CCMDs, Military Departments (MILDEPs), Defense Agencies and Field Activities$$, NULL, $$Exhibit P-40, Budget Line Item Justification: PB 2027 Defense Information Systems Agency                                                                                       Date: April 2026
