 The DISA FC/FO ensure the Department of War Information Network (DoWIN)—encompassing voice, video, and data services—aligns with the Joint Cyber Warfighting Architecture (JCWA). This alignment
 directly supports global warfighter needs across all phases of conflict.

 The FC/FO program funds DISA employee support for Combatant Commanders and Combatant Command (CCMD) staff, facilitating the integration of DISA services within Joint All-Domain Operations (JADO)
 Operational Plans (OPLANS). The IT, facility/space accommodations, and programmatic operational support at each CCMD and National Military Command Center (NMCC) Headquarters (HQ) worldwide.
 Furthermore, the FC/FO program establishes on-site strategic Command and Control (C2) and situational awareness among CCMDs, Military Departments (MILDEPs), Defense Agencies and Field Activities



