 The Ground Based Midcourse Defense (GMD) Weapon System (GWS), as the Midcourse Defense Segment of the Missile Defense System, provides the combatant commands, including United States Northern
 Command, with a continuously available (24 hours a day, 7 days a week, 365 days a year) capability for long-range missile defense of the homeland. The GWS leverages integration of Missile Defense sensors
 from across the globe and consists of a fleet of interceptors, the Ground Based Interceptors today and the Next Generation Interceptors in the future, and the enabling Ground Systems.

 As a critical component of GWS, the In Flight Interceptor Communications System Data Terminal (IDT) provides the communication link between the GMD Fire Control and In-Flight Interceptors. The Phased
 Array (PA)-IDT retrofit kits, spares, and antenna material are needed to meet emerging threats and support the capabilities of Next Generation Interceptor. A new IDT will be fielded in 2028 and will help protect
 the United States, its partners, and allies from existing and emerging threats in the Indo-Pacific Region.$$, NULL, $$Exhibit P-40, Budget Line Item Justification: PB 2027 Missile Defense Agency                                                                                                  Date: April 2026
