INSERT INTO public.proc_line_narratives (proc_line_id, fiscal_year, mission_description, justification, raw_text, source_pdf, source_page_description, source_page_amount, content_hash, ingested_at) VALUES ($$P_0300_L042$$, 2027, $$The Chairman of the Joint Chiefs of Staff (CJCS) is the principal military adviser to the President, National Security Council, and Secretary of War. The Chairman presides over and serves as a member of the
 Joint Chiefs of Staff. CJCS relies upon the Joint Staff to craft and distribute guidance for combatant forces' unified strategic direction, operations under unified commands, and integration into effective combat
 forces. On behalf of the Chairman, the Joint Staff provides Combatant Commands (CCMDs), the Services, and U.S. war fighters with joint policy, strategy, and doctrine necessary to employ effective joint combat
 forces in contingencies worldwide.

 Justification:
 The FY 2027 request for the Joint Staff includes $11,689 thousand of discretionary and zero thousand of mandatory (reconciliation) for a total of $11,689 thousand for mission critical information technology
 systems and applications investment requirements. The procurement request resources various efforts across the Joint Staff, including National Defense University (NDU).

 NDU's mission is to educate joint warfighters and other national security leaders in critical thinking and the creative application of military power to inform national strategy and globally integrated operations,
 under conditions of disruptive change, to prevail in war, peace, and competition. Sustained procurement funding is required to continue university-wide information technology and audio-visual capability
 modernization efforts to maintain DoW operating standards, deliver on the objectives in the NDU Strategic Plan, and meet accreditation requirements.

 NDU will address the following projects with $9.741 million in FY 2027 Procurement funding.
 I. Classroom Modernization ($5.400 million). This portion of funding allows NDU to sustain the audio-visual modernization project managed through the Army Corps of Engineers (ACOE), Huntsville District
 (HNC), Facility Technology Integration – General (FTI-GEN) program office. The project started in FY 2023 with a handful of classrooms in Lincoln Hall and continues to modernize the 117 classrooms across
 both campuses (Ft. McNair and NSA-Hampton Roads). The project is delivering improved audio-visual and information technology (AV/IT) system reliability and reducing cybersecurity vulnerabilities. Funding
 covers the installation of new projectors, microphones, audio controllers, cabling, and control system programming in 47 classrooms. These enhancements are transforming the student learning experience and
 improving the development of faculty teaching methods for academic delivery required by the Middle States Commission on Higher Education (MSCHE) while enabling quality Joint Professional Military Education
 (JPME) for the Chairman's University.

 II. Auditorium Modernization ($1.990 million). Funding completes the modernization effort initiated in FY 2022 through the U.S. Army Information Systems Engineering Command (USA-ISEC) that is now being
 managed by Tobyhanna Army Depot-Communication Electronics Command (TYAD-CECOM) to update NDU's ten auditoriums. FY 2027 funding will address Clarke Auditorium at NSA-Hampton Roads for the$$, NULL, $$Exhibit P-40, Budget Line Item Justification: PB 2027 The Joint Staff                                                                                                          Date: April 2026
