INSERT INTO public.proc_line_narratives (proc_line_id, fiscal_year, mission_description, justification, raw_text, source_pdf, source_page_description, source_page_amount, content_hash, ingested_at) VALUES ($$P_0300_L065$$, 2027, $$The Procurement (0300D) appropriation funds the acquisition of Department of War Education Activity (DoWEA) equipment and systems required to support mission execution and sustain operational readiness.
 This appropriation enables DoWEA to procure and modernize enterprise IT systems, cybersecurity infrastructure, and supporting platforms necessary to maintain secure, reliable, and efficient operations across
 the organization.

 Justification:
 The Enterprise-wide Point-of-Entry (POE) capability is intended to provide real-time monitoring of system and application availability across DoWEA, while delivering integrated surveillance and hardened access
 control mechanisms to safeguard schools and ensure the safety of students and staff.

 FY 2025 Status:
 Funding was provided in FY 2025 to support the POE capability. Execution is planned in alignment with facility readiness and MILCON project schedules to ensure efficient integration with ongoing infrastructure
 modernization efforts.

 FY 2026 – FY 2027 Funding Rationale:
 Funding was not requested in FY 2026 and FY 2027 due to delays in MILCON project timelines, which shifted POE implementation to the right. Prior-year resources will be executed in alignment with updated
 facility availability and project schedules.$$, NULL, $$Exhibit P-40, Budget Line Item Justification: PB 2027 Department of Defense Education Activity                                                                                 Date: April 2026
