INSERT INTO public.proc_line_narratives (proc_line_id, fiscal_year, mission_description, justification, raw_text, source_pdf, source_page_description, source_page_amount, content_hash, ingested_at) VALUES ($$P_1109_L014$$, 2027, $$Guided Multiple Launch Rocket System (GMLRS) rockets are surface-to-surface artillery rockets fired from the High Mobility Artillery Rocket System (HIMARS) launchers. GMLRS rockets provide 24/7, all-
 weather precision fires to engage both area and point targets at short, medium, and long ranges with the Army. In order to align with the National Defense Strategy and continuously deliver performance with
 affordability and speed, the Marine Corps procures its GMLRS rockets in concert with Army. The GMLRS program is critical to sustaining a Joint Force military advantage and maintaining a favorable regional
 balance of power in the theaters in which HIMARS deploys.

 Standard Range (SR): SR GMLRS consists of two variants: Unitary (U); Alternative Warhead (AW). GMLRS-U utilizes a 200-pound high explosive warhead to engage point targets with limited collateral damage.
 GMLRS-AW was developed as a non-cluster munition to engage the same target sets as dual-purpose improved conventional munition (DPICM). The GMLRS-AW rocket is 90% common with the GMLRS-U
 variant. GMLRS-U and GMLRS-AW are currently in full rate production.

 Extended Range (ER): The ER GMLRS has approximately double the range of the SR GMLRS achieving over 150km.

 The mandatory funds are for Precision Strike Missile (PrSM), a surface-to-surface, all-weather, precision-strike guided missile system designed to provided extended range to ground launched munitions on the
 battlefield. The FY 2027 mandatory funds allow the Marine Corps to procure an initial request of 10 PrSM which includes $61,335 thousands of discretionary and $15,000 thousands of mandatory (reconciliation)
 for a total of $76,335 thousands.$$, NULL, $$Exhibit P-40, Budget Line Item Justification: PB 2027 Navy                                                                                                                     Date: April 2026
