INSERT INTO public.proc_line_narratives (proc_line_id, fiscal_year, mission_description, justification, raw_text, source_pdf, source_page_description, source_page_amount, content_hash, ingested_at) VALUES ($$P_1109_L022$$, 2026, $$Global Combat Support System - Marine Corps/Logistics Chain Management (GCSS-MC/LCM) Family of Systems (FoS) serves as the primary technology for the Marine Corps Logistics Modernization strategy.

 Before GCSS-MC, the use of five outdated, separate systems that didn't talk to each other, was how the global supply chain ran. Now, this digital platform powers the entire Marine Corps logistics chain. The
 simplest way to think of it is as the Marine Corps' own private store for everything a warfighter needs to fight and win?from spare parts and fuel to ammunition and chow.

 This modern approach for the Marines on the ground enables they can find, order, and track the exact part they need from anywhere in the world. Getting their gear in the fight faster than ever before. This speed
 and accuracy provide commanders with a real-time, view of all their equipment and supplies, allowing them to make smarter, faster decisions instead of reacting to shortages. Ultimately, for the Marine Corps as
 a whole, this means operations are more efficient, cost saving with waste reduction, and significant increases to combat readiness because our logistics are finally as fast and modern as the warfighters.$$, NULL, $$Exhibit P-40, Budget Line Item Justification: PB 2027 Navy                                                                                                                     Date: April 2026
