 Description:
 Repair and Test Equipment Budget Line Item provides repair and test equipment consisting of more than 200 different items required to support the operation and maintenance of Marine Corps ground based
 weapon systems and major end items, including Marine Air-Ground Task Force (MAGTF) Logistics Support Systems (MLS2), a key CMC Force Design program enabling readiness while conducting Littoral
 Operations in Contested Environments (LOCE). These capabilities will enable ground, ordinance, and communication maintainers to perform organic maintenance activities on various Marine Corps platforms
 across widely dispersed locations that will increase the ability to sustain operational readiness levels. This portfolio also includes repair and test equipment supporting air defense systems, C2 in a degraded
 environment system, close combat lethality systems, and information warfare. It includes items such as tool kits, shop sets, manual and automatic test equipment, metrology and calibration equipment, and
 Advanced Manufacturing Systems (AMS) that includes Expeditionary Fabrication Equipment (XFAB), Tactical Fabrication Equipment (TACFAB) and Advanced Integrated Mobile Machine Shop (AIMMS).

 The following acquisition programs fall under the repair and test equipment budget line: General Purpose Tools and Test Systems (GPT&TS); MAGTF Logistics Support Systems (MLS2); Advanced
 Manufacturing System (AMS); Automatic Test Systems (ATS), Calibration and Maintenance Program (CAMP), and Conditioned Based Maintenance (CBM+).

 General Purpose Tools and Test Systems (GPT&TS) represents three separate program efforts that provide the Marine Corps with over 110 different types of Test Equipment and Tool Kits/Shop Sets. Over
 40,000 fielded systems are used on a daily basis by over 24,000 Marine maintainers to support expeditionary field-level maintenance of ground equipment throughout all of the Ground Combat Element (GCE),
 Logistics Combat Element (LCE), and in some of the Aviation Combat Element (ACE) units. GPT&TS includes the family of General-Purpose Electronic Test Equipment (GPETE), family of General-Purpose
 Mechanical Test Equipment (GPMTE), and family of Tool Sets & Kits (TS&K). GPT&TS test equipment ranges from hand-held multimeters to room sized engine and transmission dynamometers. Tool sets
 range from an individual mechanics toolbox to High Mobility Multipurpose Wheeled Vehicle (HMMWV) mounted shelters to 20-foot containerized tool room sets.

 MAGTF Logistics Support Systems (MLS2) enhances maintenance readiness across the distributed Fleet Marine Force, directly increasing operational readiness. As a Force Design, EABO, and CBM+ enabler,
 the EMSS component of MLS2 provides a rugged, lightweight, one-man portable maintenance aid (EMSS hardware kits) that significantly improves combat service support for both garrisoned and deployed
 MAGTF forces. EMSS provides users with diagnostic capabilities for over 70 ground weapon platforms, utilizing both Commercial Off-The-Shelf (COTS) and Government Off-The-Shelf (GOTS) software,
 and provides access to essential technical manuals and publications. Connected EMSS assets facilitate online supply and maintenance transactions via GCSS, Mobile Field Service, and other online tools.
 EMSS emulates and interfaces with test equipment, providing access to Interactive Electronic Technical Manuals (IETMs), Computer Based Training (CBT), and other critical maintenance applications. EMSS
 connects to the Marine Corps Enterprise Network (MCEN), enabling access to defense business systems i.e. Global Combat Support System - Marine Corps (GCSS-MC) for streamlined maintenance and supply
 transactions, ultimately maximizing operational readiness.



